name: Wild Mood Swings
description: Wild Mood Swings is the tenth studio album by British alternative rock band The Cure, released on 7 May 1996 through record label Fiction. Wild Mood Swings charted at number nine in the UK Albums Chart, staying on chart for six weeks, and charted at number 12 in the US Billboard 200. Four singles were released from the album, the first being "The 13th", released in April 1996, followed by "Mint Car" released in June, "Strange Attraction" released in United States in October and "Gone!" released in Europe in December 1996.
